Virtual Scrolling (Infinite Scroll)
If you want the grid to automatically load the next page when the user scrolls down, you need to enable virtual scrolling and configure the DataSource for server-side paging.

Example:

csharp
@(Html.Kendo().Grid<YourModel>()
    .Name("VehicleGrid")
    .Columns(columns =>
    {
        columns.Bound(c => c.VehicleName);
        columns.Command(cmd => cmd.Custom("Delete").Click("showDeleteConfirmation"));
    })
    .Scrollable(s => s.Virtual(true).Height("400px")) // Virtual scrolling enabled
    .DataSource(ds => ds.Ajax()
        .PageSize(50) // How many rows to load at a time
        .ServerOperation(true) // Server-side paging
        .Read(r => r.Action("GetVehicles", "Vehicles"))
    )
)
Key points for virtual scroll to work:

.Scrollable(s => s.Virtual(true).Height("...")) â€” must have a fixed height, not "auto".

DataSource must have:

.ServerOperation(true) (or .ServerPaging(true) in some versions)

.PageSize(...) set
